%N A112401 1-digit squares with their digits reversed, then 2-digit squares reversed, and so on, including squares zero-padded on the left but excluding squares ending in 0.
%e A112401 The sequence represents the squares (1, 4, 9), (01, 04, 09, 16, 25, 36, 49, 64, 81), (001, 004, 009, 016, 025, 036, 049, 064, 081, 121, 144, 169, ...), each entry zero-padded to the left as necessary, then reversed. Note 100 does not appear, since squares with a trailing 0 are ignored.
